{
  "info": {
    "name": "Restaurant App API",
    "_postman_id": "restaurant-app-collection-v3",
    "description": "Full API collection for the Restaurant App backend.\n\n## Quick start\n\n1. Replace the URL host (`https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api`) with your actual API Gateway base URL in each request that you use. Stage `api` must be in the path; no trailing slash.\n2. Run **Auth → Sign In**, copy the returned `access_token` and `refresh_token`.\n3. In any authenticated request, replace `YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN` in the `Authorization` header with the real token.\n4. Replace the example UUIDs (`reservation_id`, `location_id`) in URLs with the ones you actually want to query.\n\n`{\"message\": \"Missing Authentication Token\"}` from AWS means the path didn't match a deployed route — most often a missing `/api` stage prefix or a trailing slash.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints – sign-up, sign-in, token refresh, logout.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Sign Up",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Jane\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"jane.doe@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password1!\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api/auth/sign-up",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["your-api-id", "execute-api", "us-east-1", "amazonaws", "com"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-up"]
            },
            "description": "Register a new user. Role is assigned automatically (Customer by default; Waiter if the email appears in the waiter-emails table; Admin if listed in the admin-emails table).\n\n### Body fields\n| Field | Type | Required | Rules |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `firstName` | string | yes | 1-100 chars |\n| `lastName` | string | yes | 1-100 chars |\n| `email` | string | yes | Valid email; local part must start with a letter |\n| `password` | string | yes | 8-16 chars, ≥1 uppercase, ≥1 lowercase, ≥1 digit, ≥1 special char |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"a1b2c3d4-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n  \"message\": \"User registered successfully\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "422 Unprocessable Entity",
              "status": "Unprocessable Entity",
              "code": 422,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"errors\": [\n    { \"field\": \"password\", \"message\": \"must contain at least one uppercase letter\" }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign In",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"jane.doe@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password1!\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api/auth/sign-in",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["your-api-id", "execute-api", "us-east-1", "amazonaws", "com"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-in"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate a user and receive an access token + refresh token.\n\n**Lockout:** After 5 failed attempts the account is locked for 15 minutes.\n\n### Body fields\n| Field | Type | Required |\n|---|---|---|\n| `email` | string | yes |\n| `password` | string | yes |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"refresh_token\": \"eyJjdHkiOiJKV1QiLCJlbmMiOiJBMjU2R0NNIiwiYWxnIjoiUlNBLU9BRVAifQ...\",\n  \"username\": \"jane.doe@example.com\",\n  \"role\": \"Customer\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"Invalid credentials\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "423 Locked",
              "status": "Locked",
              "code": 423,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"Account locked. Try again later.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api/auth/refresh",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["your-api-id", "execute-api", "us-east-1", "amazonaws", "com"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Exchange a refresh token for a new access token.\n\n### Body fields\n| Field | Type | Required |\n|---|---|---|\n| `refresh_token` | string | yes |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api/auth/logout",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["your-api-id", "execute-api", "us-east-1", "amazonaws", "com"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Invalidate the refresh token to end the session.\n\n### Body fields\n| Field | Type | Required |\n|---|---|---|\n| `refresh_token` | string | yes |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"Logged out successfully\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
